The paper focuses on influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer science and social sciences. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for influence maximization, which involves computational optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between accuracy and scalability, which is a common issue in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
